TASK: Create the Canvas Build presenter — a pure function that transforms BuildPayload into a view model for the orbital UI.

CONTEXT:
- BuildPayload contains: build_graph (nodes, edges), build_issues, binding_ledger, import_snapshots, authority_attachments, projection_status, compiled_spec_projection.
- BuildNode has: node_id, kind (step/gate/state), title, summary, route, status, required_inputs, outputs, binding_ids, issue_ids.
- The UI renders nodes in an orbital path (center of screen), with ring colors indicating state.

WHAT TO DO:

Create `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/canvasBuildPresenter.ts`:

```typescript
import type { BuildPayload, BuildNode } from '../shared/types';

export interface OrbitNode {
  id: string;
  kind: 'step' | 'gate' | 'state';
  title: string;
  summary: string;
  glyphType: GlyphType;
  ringState: RingState;
  position: { x: number; y: number; angle: number };
  badges: Badge[];
  isSelected: boolean;
  isOnDominantPath: boolean;
}

export type GlyphType = 'step' | 'gate' | 'state' | 'trigger' | 'human' | 'binding';
export type RingState = 'grounded' | 'selected' | 'projected' | 'blocked';
export type Badge = 'branch' | 'parallel' | 'loop';

export interface OrbitEdge {
  id: string;
  from: string;
  to: string;
  type: string;
  isOnDominantPath: boolean;
}

export interface DockContent {
  actionOptions: ActionOption[];
  contextAttachments: ContextItem[];
  connectBindings: ConnectItem[];
}

export interface ReleaseStatus {
  readiness: 'ready' | 'blocked' | 'draft';
  blockers: { message: string; severity: string; nodeIds: string[] }[];
  projectedJobs: { label: string; agent: string }[];
  projectedTriggers: { type: string; source: string }[];
}

export interface CanvasBuildViewModel {
  nodes: OrbitNode[];
  edges: OrbitEdge[];
  dominantPath: string[];
  release: ReleaseStatus;
  dockContent: DockContent | null;
  totalNodes: number;
  resolvedNodes: number;
  blockedNodes: number;
}

export function presentBuild(
  payload: BuildPayload | null,
  selectedNodeId: string | null,
  orbitRadius: number
): CanvasBuildViewModel
```

The function must:
1. Extract dominant path from compiled_spec_projection.jobs mapped back to node IDs. Fallback to main ordered chain from build_graph edges.
2. Position nodes along an elliptical orbit based on their index in the dominant path. Non-path nodes positioned as satellites.
3. Map node status to ringState: ready->grounded, blocked->blocked, draft->projected. Selected node gets 'selected'.
4. Map node kind/route to glyphType.
5. Populate dockContent for the selected node: action options from node's route/kind, context from authority_attachments filtered to that node, connect from binding_ledger filtered to that node.
6. Populate release from build_issues, projection_status, compiled_spec_projection.

RULES:
- PURE FUNCTION. No side effects, no React, no fetch, no DOM.
- Must be independently testable.
- Include a test file canvasBuildPresenter.test.ts with at least 4 tests.

OUTPUT: New: canvas/canvasBuildPresenter.ts, canvas/canvasBuildPresenter.test.ts

TASK: Create the Canvas Build reducer for UI state management.

WHAT TO DO:

Create `Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/canvasBuildReducer.ts`:

```typescript
export interface CanvasBuildState {
  selectedNodeId: string | null;
  openDock: 'action' | 'context' | 'connect' | null;
  dockTab: string | null;
  stepperStage: number;
  stepperPath: string[];
  releaseOpen: boolean;
  orbitZoom: number;
  focusedHint: string | null;
}

export type CanvasBuildAction =
  | { type: 'SELECT_NODE'; nodeId: string | null }
  | { type: 'OPEN_DOCK'; dock: 'action' | 'context' | 'connect' }
  | { type: 'CLOSE_DOCK' }
  | { type: 'SET_DOCK_TAB'; tab: string }
  | { type: 'SET_STEPPER_STAGE'; stage: number }
  | { type: 'STEPPER_NEXT' }
  | { type: 'STEPPER_BACK' }
  | { type: 'TOGGLE_RELEASE' }
  | { type: 'SET_ZOOM'; zoom: number }
  | { type: 'SET_HINT'; hint: string | null }
  | { type: 'RESET' };

export const initialCanvasBuildState: CanvasBuildState = { ... };

export function canvasBuildReducer(state: CanvasBuildState, action: CanvasBuildAction): CanvasBuildState
```

Key behaviors:
- SELECT_NODE: sets selectedNodeId, closes dock, resets stepper
- OPEN_DOCK: sets openDock, only one dock open at a time
- CLOSE_DOCK: clears openDock
- STEPPER_NEXT/BACK: increment/decrement stepperStage within stepperPath bounds
- TOGGLE_RELEASE: toggles releaseOpen (independent of side dock — can coexist)
- RESET: returns to initialCanvasBuildState

Include canvasBuildReducer.test.ts with tests for:
- Single dock open rule
- Node selection resets dock
- Stepper bounds checking
- Release coexists with dock

